    by deriving $K _ C$ from $(K _ A, K _ B)$, * as $K _ B $ is
    kept permanently with the user's contact details. However,
    in an extension to the proctoll, it is planned to either quickly
    separate the $K _ B$ key from the contact details, or to asymmetrically
    encrypt it and give another party control over decryption.
    It was therefore left in the protocol.
